2012-12-31|2013-01-06.description: Concluding the two-part re-imagining of the classic "Mirror Universe" episode! Don't miss this radical transformation of Kirk & Co., as events unfold leading up to next summer's STAR TREK sequel! Overseen by STAR TREK writer/producer Roberto Orci!
2012-12-31|2013-01-06.name: Mirrored, Part 2

2012-12-31|2013-01-06.description: Bartman discovers a Japanese comic book at the Android's Dungeon depicting some of his greatest exploits in manga form. And then in a crisis of discontinuous continuities, Plasmo taps into a neighboring dimension to find a replacement for a fallen Superior Squadron comrade, causing a calamitous chain reaction and a world overpopulated with duplicate heroes and villains.
2012-12-31|2013-01-06.name: Bartmanga!; Crisis of Discontinuous Continuities

2012-01-02|2012-01-08.description:
"Archie Marries Veronica" - Kevin returns from battle a war hero and the whole gang have assembled to watch him tie the knot! However it's not wedded bliss for all in attendance as the sting of separation from Veronica continues to pain Archie. Working class couple Reggie and Betty field an offer to star in a reality program showcasing their entrepreneurial nature while Dilton hatches a scheme with Mr. Lodge!

"Archie Marries Betty" - Kevin's wedding is upon us and you're on the guest list! But how exactly did Kevin meet his significant other? Discover how right in these pages... Meanwhile Archie juggles teaching responsibilities with his marriage to Betty. Don't miss out on the wedding event of the year that everyone's talking about!

Proper Japanese Title: Shinjin to Veteran (新人とベテラン)

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 134: Running Solo and Slow Footedness (独走と鈍足 Dokusō to Donsoku)
  • Chapter 135: Succession and Interference (連続と阻止 Renzoku to Soshi)
  • Chapter 136: Extensions and Countermeasures (伸びしろと対抗策 Nobishiro to Taikōsaku)
  • Chapter 137: Lead Color and Center Color (巻頭カラーとセンターカラー Kantō Karā to Sentā Karā)
  • Chapter 138: Power and Idea (迫力とアイディア Hakuryoku to Aidia)
  • Chapter 139: Final Chapter and Comments (最終話とコメント Saishūwa to Komento)
  • Chapter 140: Limits and Phoenix (限界と火の鳥 Genkai to Hi no Tori)
  • Chapter 141: Age and Achievements (年齢と実績 Nenrei to Jisseki)
  • Chapter 142: Newcomers and Veterans (新人とベテラン Shinjin to Beteran)
2012-01-02|2012-01-08.name: Shinjin to Veteran

volume.name: Shi ga Futari wo Wakatsu made

2012-01-30|2012-02-05.description: The action in Penguin's fighting pit becomes electric as Bane and Grundy face off! Bane may be in search of the Titan drug, but with Grundy possessed by his own stimulant, there's no telling who will win.
2012-01-30|2012-02-05.name: Theatre of Violence (Part 3)

2012-02-06|2012-02-12.description: It's Valentine's Day, and love is in the air. But so is a whole lot of sheer magical insanity, because Batgirl has a not-so-secret admirer: Bat-Mite!
2012-02-06|2012-02-12.name: Love At First Mite

volume.name: The All-New Batman: The Brave and the Bold

2012-02-13|2012-02-19.description:
Zero finally shows his true colors.

A battle rages on Utopia!

2012-02-27|2012-03-04.description:
Proper Japanese Title: Shiai Shuryo (試合終了！！)

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 136: I'll Win!! (絶対勝つ！！ Zettee Katsu!!)
  • Chapter 137: Like I'd Lose (負けるかよ Makerukayo)
  • Chapter 138: But the One I Believe in is (信じてるのは Shinjiterunowa)
  • Chapter 139: Game Over!! (試合終了！！ Taimu Appu!!)
  • Chapter 140: I'm Really Glad (本当によかった Hontou ni Yokatta)
  • Chapter 141: Nice To Meet You! (Nice to Meet You! (よろしくな！） Nice To Meet You! (Yoroshikuna!))
  • Chapter 142: Please Teach Me (教えてください Oshietekudasai)
  • Chapter 143: It Couldn't Be Easy (軽いものなはずないだろう Karuimonona Hazunaidarou)
  • Chapter 144: It'll Be Fun (楽しみじゃい Tanoshimijai)
2012-02-27|2012-03-04.name: Time Up!!

2012-03-12|2012-03-18.description: John Carter is finally united with the son he never knew. The two of them face bloody death in the great arena of Issus, Goddess of Life Eternal. No one has ever escaped from the arena of Issus before, but Carter and his son might have a thing or two to teach this false goddess about religion -- the old fashioned way, at the end of a sword point! Hair-raising escapes, devious villainy, and an embarrassing revelation or two await you in Warlord of Mars Issue 16: Flight and Pursuit!
2012-03-12|2012-03-18.name: Gods of Mars, Part 4: Flight and Pursuit

2012-03-12|2012-03-18.description:
Chapter Titles

  • Episode 131: Time Limit
  • Episode 132: Diagnosis
  • Episode 133: Death to Approach
  • Episode 134: Unbelievable Prediction
  • Episode 135: Way Back
  • Episode 136: Secret of the Tower
  • Episode 137: High Play
  • Episode 138: Decision
  • Episode 139: Strong Band
2012-03-12|2012-03-18.name: Vol. 16

2012-03-12|2012-03-18.description:
Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 147. "Elopement" (逃避行 "Tōhikō")
  • Chapter 148. "The Long Confinement" (かくも長き籠城 "Kakumo Nagaki Rōjō")
  • Chapter 149. "About Me." (私について。 "Watashi ni Tsuite.")
  • Chapter 150. "Welcome Hell" (地獄へようこそ "Jigoku e yōkoso")

2012-03-26|2012-04-01.description: Epilogue. The Fallout of the Forever and Doom storylines. A new direction for the Future Foundation and Marvel's First Family.
2012-03-26|2012-04-01.name: One Step Beyond

2012-04-02|2012-04-08.description: The explosive, final battle for the Under Realm begins! After Lady Death’s nearly-impossible victory over Behemoth, the forces who oppose the twisted rule of Death Queen are at last united, and make preparations to strike back against the blood-thirsty conqueror. But before they can begin to formulate a strategy, Lady Death, Stigmata, Valora, and the meager forces of the rebellion come under siege from Death Queen’s incredible war-machines and a legion of flesh-eating zombie soldiers who accompanied Behemoth to their secret location. Hopelessly outnumbered and completely surrounded, Lady Death’s final fight against the insane military conquest of her own mother commences! Death Queen has plans of her own, however, as she unveils to Tormina a fail-safe, Doomsday scenario which will ensure her victory... Available with a Regular or Sultry cover by Matt Martin a Wraparound by Richard Ortiz and a retailer order incentive Art Deco covers by painter Michael Dipascale!

Archie in "Charity Ball!" - Veronica signs the gang up to play in her father's charity baseball game benefitting the march of dimes! Fly balls and home runs abound as the team pulls together earning more money for the charity each time they score! How much will the team manage to raise by the final inning? Find out in these pages!

Dilton in "Brain Buster" - The gang takes turns testing out Dilton's new invention - a phone with artificial intelligence! After a couple test runs go awry, will the phone prove its worth in Archie's hands or end in catastrophe?
2012-04-02|2012-04-08.name: Charity Ball / Brain Buster

2012-04-09|2012-04-15.description: Here's what we can tell you: Tom Judge and his companion, clairvoyant Tilly Grimes have discovered something is wrong with the world. Their discovery has prompted them to embark on a mission to track down the bearers of the 13 Artifacts. But isn't that what caused problems the last time?
2012-04-09|2012-04-15.name: New Creation, Part 3

2012-04-16|2012-04-22.description:
A Routine Prisoner Transfer Of The Fly Thrusts Venom Into One Of The Most Dire Conflicts Of His Young Super Career!

One Fatal Act Will Change Venom’s Life Forever – And Lead To Savage Consequences In The Months To Come!
2012-04-16|2012-04-22.name: Clemency

2012-04-16|2012-04-22.description: In an ancient, abandoned city, Vampirella faces betrayal by an ally, a terrible loss, and the return of an old foe. Don't miss the darkest chapter yet in Dynamite Entertainment's acclaimed horror-adventure series.

This special arc by Eisner-nominated writer Joshua Hale Fialkov concludes! The Silurian plan is revealed, apocalypse imminent, and with mere minutes to go, can the Doctor and his strange new ally save not just Casablanca but the entire human race?
2012-04-16|2012-04-22.name: As Time Goes By, Part 4

2012-04-23|2012-04-29.description: Despite Kuro and Mana’s best efforts, the two high mototsumitama are no match for Shion, one of Reishin Shishigami’s top generals. Amused by Mana’s arrogance, Shion reveals that the proud purebloods are actually an impure breed descended from the original mototsumitama, who gave up the purity of their race in order to survive. Without the powerful battle genes of her ancestors, Kuro cannot hope to defeat Shion, let alone Reishin. Filled with rage, Kuro launches a ferocious attack unlike anything the others have ever seen. Has Kuro unlocked some hidden power of her own, or will this sudden surge of bloodlust take her out of commission for good?!
2012-04-23|2012-04-29.name: Vol. 16

2012-04-23|2012-04-29.description:
VANESSA NEVER STOPS MAKING US LAUGH!

Vanessa is in top shape and surrounded by her friends for our greatest pleasure.

36 pages of gags, each one funnier and more biting than the one before! Vanessa just never stops making her readers laugh!
2012-04-23|2012-04-29.name: Blonde attitude

2012-04-30|2012-05-06.description: Samantha, Baba Yaga, the Dark One and The Sea Witch... What do these four powerful beings have in common? Each are searching for falsebloods who dwell on earth in preparation of a war that looms on the horizon. And what part will the rogue Beast play in the final end game? The seeds are planted and secrets are revealed in this not to be missed issue! From the creative minds behind the Wonderland trilogy and Dream Eater saga comes the story that sets the stage for the next evolution of the Grimm universe.
2012-04-30|2012-05-06.name: The Gathering, Part 1 of 2

2012-04-30|2012-05-06.description: Comics Revue Presents features 'Rick O'Shay' by Stan Lynde; The Phantom in 'Fathers and Sons'' Mandrake the Magician in 'Peril Road'' Flash Gordon by Mac Raboy; Latigo by Stan Lynde; Tarzan by Russ Manning; Gasoline Alley by Dick Moores; Steve Canyon by Milton Caniff; and Casey Ruggles by Warren Tufts.
2012-04-30|2012-05-06.name: Phantom

2012-05-07|2012-05-13.description: Akane is determined to face Akram on his own turf, but within the sacred cave of the Demon Clan nothing is as it seems. With her friends in mortal danger, Akane has no choice but to sacrifice her own life. Meanwhile, Tenma and Shimon may have lost their memories of the Capital, but their feelings for Akane are stronger than ever. Can they find her before it's too late?
2012-05-07|2012-05-13.name: Vol. 16

2012-05-07|2012-05-13.description: Jabbar the Powerful's little sister wants in on the superhero adventure and forms her own superhero team with the youngest and newest members of The 99. There's a gem-bearer in trouble beneath the streets of Paris - but what can a couple of kids do? Find out as we introduce, the Junior 99!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 64: Let's Have A Christmas Party!
  • Chapter 65: Together With Everyone
  • Chapter 66: Complications
  • Chapter 67: Uncontrollable Feelings

2012-05-28|2012-06-03.description: Evilheart and Pureheart may have met their match when they take on The Dude! With a trick cane and a cunning criminal mind to his advantage, The Dude keeps the duo at bay until he has them right where he wants them! Will the super teens manage to bring the jewel thief to justice or will they fall prey to the dastardly evil-doer? Find out in 'Chaos in a Common Cane!'
2012-05-28|2012-06-03.name: Chaos in a Common Cane

2012-05-28|2012-06-03.description:
Robin, Kid Flash and Artemis fight crime with their adult counterparts!

Guest starring Batman, The Flash and Green Arrow!

First part of a new storyline.
2012-05-28|2012-06-03.name: Common Denominators

2012-06-04|2012-06-10.description:
Rick discovers that there are communities of survivors nearby, and begins to explore a larger world.

Collects THE WALKING DEAD #91-96.
2012-06-04|2012-06-10.name: A Larger World

2012-06-04|2012-06-10.description: Guest writer, JUSTIN JORDAN (THE STRANGE TALENT OF LUTHER STRODE) brings his strange talent for gore and horror to Hack/Slash! Vlad and Cassie must travel back to Chicago in search of Vlad's elusive mutant family to find a cure. If Vlad's disease doesn't kill him, his aunt, cousin and grandpa just might! Also includes an installment of the serial "The Corpse: Orphans of the Air" by James Lowder and Steve Bryant.
2012-06-04|2012-06-10.name: The Good Son, Part 1

2012-06-25|2012-07-01.description:
Transformed into…the DECONSECRATOR!

Enchantress and her Keep unleashed upon a slumbering Asgardia!

Besieged in dreams and in waking life! When will this nightmare ever end…?

2012-07-09|2012-07-15.description: Get up and move with Betty and Veronica! The girls are experts on staying in shape, and they're ready to share their secrets with you! Join them and the rest of the Riverdale gang as they jog, swim, hit the gym, ride bikes, and even do some rock climbing. Can Betty & Veronica whip the rest of the gang into shape? Who will win the triathalon: Archie or Chuck? And can ANYONE get Jughead off his lazy butt?! Stretch out those laugh muscles and find out!
2012-07-09|2012-07-15.name: Betty & Veronica Fitness Fun!

2012-07-16|2012-07-22.description:
AVX TIE-INS!

We can’t say much or we spoil the event of the summer!

The X-Men move against the forces of SINISTER!
2012-07-16|2012-07-22.name: This Strange Unpleasant Land, Part 2

2012-07-16|2012-07-22.description:
"SIX SHOOTER ON THE SEVEN SEAS," Part Four

Ancient evil has arisen aboard the pirate ship called the Mermaid's Bottom in this, the penultimate part of our 3rd story arc. Mind-control, maidens, monsters, meat, and more words that start with "M". Everybody say it with me now: "Mmmmmmmmm..."
2012-07-16|2012-07-22.name: Six Shooter on the Seven Seas: Part 4

2012-07-23|2012-07-29.description: It was supposed to be so simple... The battle lines have been drawn, and each side has taken major casualties. Captain Elliott Spencer has shown his hand, and now Kirsty Cotton makes her last stand. With her allies fallen, Kirsty will be asked to make the ultimate sacrifice. Don't miss this arc-ending issue that dives deeper into the sordid world of Clive Barker!
2012-07-23|2012-07-29.name: Hell Hath No Fury, Part Four

2012-07-23|2012-07-29.description: Writer Daryl Gregory and artist Carlos Magno continue their critically acclaimed run and deliver an arc-ending issue you'll never forget! Alaya must rally her remaining forces against a threat, one even greater than Sully's troop of rebelling humans…one that might come from the highest echelons of Ape society!
2012-07-23|2012-07-29.name: The Half Man, Part 4

2012-07-30|2012-08-05.description:
Nelson/Murdock no more! Foggy’s discovered a secret Matt’s been keeping--and he doesn’t take it well!

And a last page shock that will have Daredevil fans buzzing!

Series Stalwarts Mark Waid and Chris Samnee bring you a turning point in the lives of Marvel’s most famous legal team!

2012-08-06|2012-08-12.description:
Discordian cells attack American interests all over the world!

Shock journalist Reed Braxton is turning the public against the Sentinel of Liberty.

But if Reed Braxton is dead, who the heck is that on LIVE television?
2012-08-06|2012-08-12.name: New World Orders, Part 2

2012-08-06|2012-08-12.description: On the eve of her big music competition, Kahoko should be getting some much-needed sleep…but she can’t stop thinking about Len. When Len reveals just how soon he’s leaving to study abroad, suddenly Kahoko can’t concentrate on music. Can she and Len admit how much they mean to each other before it’s too late? And can Kahoko still turn in a performance worthy of her training?
2012-08-06|2012-08-12.name: Vol. 16

2012-08-06|2012-08-12.description: "Spiritus ex Machina" – the epic conclusion! The debate over the future of robotics reaches an explosive turning point, and with multiple lives hanging in the balance, the Robot Masters race against time to save their creators. Will one make the ultimate sacrifice to save their comrades? And will Dr. Lalinde’s tragic secret finally be revealed? Meanwhile, Dr. Wily welcomes the newest robot to his army - who is Break Man?
2012-08-06|2012-08-12.name: Spiritus Ex Machina, Part Four: Whatever It Takes

2012-08-13|2012-08-19.description: DEEP TERROR concludes! Scarlett and Team Bravo are trapped a mile beneath the Earth’s surface with an army of COBRA killers beneath on their tail! Their only hope is—Mainframe? Also: COBRA’s too-public campaign to destroy the Joes rolls on. How can America’s super-secret heroes survive in the light of day?
2012-08-13|2012-08-19.name: Deep Terror; Conclusion

2012-08-20|2012-08-26.description: THE HUNT IS ON! The key to all of Cobra's secrets is in the crossfire as FLINT's secret G.I. Joe squad converges on FIREFLY and BLACKLIGHT! Everyone has their own agenda-and everybody has a lot of guns! It's not-stop action and betrayal as secrets come to light and bodies hit the floor!
2012-08-20|2012-08-26.name: Son of the Snake, Part 4; The Hunt is On!

2012-08-20|2012-08-26.description: Translates Hulk #45-46 and Incredible Hulk #4-7.

2012-08-27|2012-09-02.description: SERPENT'S SHADOW concludes here in the lair of the COBRA Commander! Snake Eyes, Storm shadow and the murderous Rika must free themselves from a trap set by the Commander in the only way they know how-KILL their way out! Will Snake Eyes show his hand and reveal his betrayal of the Arashikage or play this round out to the end?
2012-08-27|2012-09-02.name: Serpent's Shadow Conclusion

2012-09-03|2012-09-09.deck: French translation and collection of issues #91-96
2012-09-03|2012-09-09.description: French translation and collection of issues #91-96; the English trade can be found here.
2012-09-03|2012-09-09.name: Un vaste monde

2012-09-10|2012-09-16.description: UNITED WE STAND! The X-Men fight for their lives in the Sentinel-controlled states. Featuring, Nick Fury's Howling Kittens?
2012-09-10|2012-09-16.name: United We Stand; Chapter One

2012-09-10|2012-09-16.description: The Hellfire Club is on the run from Cyclops and rest of the Phoenix Five. How does an anti-mutant organization operate in a mutant-run world?
2012-09-10|2012-09-16.name: The Fires of Hell A-Glowing

2012-09-10|2012-09-16.description: Superman battles Batman at Stryker Island prison--and it's not as one-sided a confrontation as you might think! Meanwhile, Nightwing mixes it up with Green Arrow.
2012-09-10|2012-09-16.name: Detective Part 4

2012-09-17|2012-09-23.description:
True-crime writer Phil Stanford tells a gritty tale from Portland’s underbelly as he kicks off City of Roses with artist Patric Reynolds—a new era for the Crime Does Not Pay name!

Plus, Richard Corben adapts a spine-tingling story by Edgar Allan Poe!

Story & Chapter Titles

  • Crime Does Not Pay presents: City of Roses - Chapter 1
  • The Girl with the Keyhole Eyes - Chapter 2
  • The Deep Sea - Chapter 1
  • Finder: Third World - Chapter 14
  • Concrete Park - Book 1: "You Send Me" -Chapter 6
  • Edgar Allen Poe's Berenice
  • Buddy Cops - Chapter 3
  • Riven - Chapter 3
  • Dead Air
2012-09-17|2012-09-23.name: City of Roses; The Girl with Keyhole Eyes; The Deep Sea; Finder: Third World; Concrete Park; EA Poe's Berenice; Buddy Cops; Riven; Dead Air

2012-09-17|2012-09-23.description: "Gotham Spirit" part 1 of 1. Batman's unique relationship with Gotham City and her underworld is a gritty and beautiful thing...as four armed robbers are about to find out!
2012-09-17|2012-09-23.name: Gotham Spirt, Part 1 of 1

2012-09-24|2012-09-30.description: Add another baby to your SPAWN: ORIGINS family and re-live the excitement of one of the best-selling independent comics of all time! Collecting classic issues of everyone's favorite antihero and featuring impossible pencils by GREG CAPULLO, this is the stuff legends are made of. While Spawn is busy battling his inner demons, real demons are on the prowl and want a piece of him, too. Enter the historic battle with Urizen and the advent of Ab and Zab. Plus... Wanda's pregnant?! Collects Spawn #93-98.
2012-09-24|2012-09-30.name: Volume 16

2012-09-24|2012-09-30.description: The Punisher and Cole reach a shared conclusion. Prepare for the War Zone.
United We Stand. The heroes of the Ultimate Universe must come together to save the United States from its darkest days yet.
2012-09-24|2012-09-30.name: United We Stand, Part One: The Call of the People

2012-10-01|2012-10-07.description: While still in her self-imposed exile, Dejah Thoris becomes entangled with an Okar warrior from the North in a dangerous battle of survival!

2012-10-15|2012-10-21.description:
UNITED WE STAND CONCLUSION

Miles' father goes to the detention area while the whole city is in chaos.

Meanwhile, Spider-Man has invaded The Triskelion and looks foward to join the Ultimates.

ALSO IN THIS ISSUE:

New president elected!
2012-10-15|2012-10-21.name: United We Stand; Part 2

2012-10-22|2012-10-28.description:
David Hine and artist George Duarte have created a story that takes all of our fears about interpersonal relationships and throws them in a bloody blender. It's no longer an exercise in self-discovery for our group of egotistical young writers. Now it's a lesson in survival and sheer horror as they see their hidden inner desires and excesses turned real as the Crossed virus lets them look at the monsters within.

There is no hope.

There is no help.

There is only the Crossed.

2012-10-29|2012-11-04.description:
This 16th issue of Zarjaz contains the following stories:

  • Anderson- I Death. 6 pages
  • BAD COMPANY- Krool Intentions. 4 pages
  • Flesh-FutureShock. 4 pages
  • JD- Sleepers Awake. 10 pages
  • Sinister Dexter- Dr Maybes Museum. 3 pages
  • Slaine-Night Moves. 6 pages
  • Tales of the GI- In The Zone 3. 5 pages
  • The Hills Of Hellfire, My Dear. 8 pages
  • Whatever Happened to… Sancho Panzer? 6 pages

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 105: Causes of Breaking
  • Chapter 106: Causes of Breaking II
  • Chapter 107: Causes of Breaking III
  • Chapter 108: A Grandfather's Thoughts
  • Chapter 109: Old Memories
  • Chapter 110: A Risky Situation
  • Chapter 111: A Risky Situation II
  • Chapter 112: Unsolicited
2012-10-29|2012-11-04.name: Vol. 16

2012-10-29|2012-11-04.description:
GEN 16, Indie Manga from the Tokyo Underground, features Anomal. Weird tales of horror and the bizarre are part of a peculiar vision of the world in this collection of short stories. GEN 16 also features,the story of a killer, a man known only as Psycho. And Android Angels, tales from a land beyond, where androids not only protect humans, but also live and get intimate with them.

Contents

  • Psycho
  • Android Angels
  • Stones of Power
  • Anomal
  • Alive

2012-11-05|2012-11-11.description:
Eiji Nizuma announces that if he can top the Weekly Shonen Jump survey results for ten straight weeks, he will have one of the manga series in the magazine canceled. But which series does Eiji want to cancel? And what will Ashirogi and the other manga creators do to stop him?!

Chapter Titles

  • Ch. 134: Front Runner and Slow Runner
  • Ch. 135: Consecutive and Prevention
  • Ch. 136: Potential and Counterplan
  • Ch. 137: Front Color and Center Color
  • Ch. 138: Aggressive and Idea
  • Ch. 139: Final Chapter and Comment
  • Ch. 140: Limit and Phoenix
  • Ch. 141: Age and Achievement
  • Ch. 142: Rookie and Veteran
2012-11-05|2012-11-11.name: Rookie and Veteran

2012-11-26|2012-12-02.description: Angel’s plan to resurrect Giles inches ever closer toward success. As he and Faith hack their way toward one more magical item to help in their venture, Angel reveals it is time to get the final part of Giles’s soul. But their triumphant return to London holds more than one surprise: first, the revenge-seeking Nadira and the Slayers come calling . . .
2012-11-26|2012-12-02.name: Death and Consequences, Part 1

2012-11-26|2012-12-02.description: A relentless, demented foe finds the Turtles and he won't rest until his deadly mission is fulfilled! A desperate fight for survival will take some unexpected turns before the night is over. Don't miss it!

2012-12-03|2012-12-09.description: Following the conclusion of "Konstriction," this Beyond Origins chapter gives us a very special look at the exiled New God--Barda!
2012-12-03|2012-12-09.name: Beyond Origins: Barda

2012-12-10|2012-12-16.description: Buffy takes on the zompire epidemic in San Francisco with new allies—the SFPD and Billy the Vampire Slayer! Just as Buffy finds contentment in her life, she's torn from routine battle and forced to confront an ancient demon from her former lover's past!
2012-12-10|2012-12-16.name: Welcome To The Team Part One

volume.name: Buffy the Vampire Slayer Season Nine

2012-12-10|2012-12-16.description: After several tough cases, the Ghostbusters are ready for a real day off from dealing with the supernatural... but that doesn't necessarily mean the supernatural is going to take a day off from them. Ready to settle in and do some relaxing, they are surprised as a spectral child appears before them, speaking one word before it disappears -- help.

When Doc Ido, a talented cyber-physician, finds Alita's head in a junk heap, she has lost all memory of her past life. But when he reconstructs her, she discovers her body still instinctively remembers the Panzer Kunst, the most powerful cyborg fighting technique ever known. In the postapocalyptic world of the Scrapyard, as the secrets of Alita's past unfold, each day is a struggle for survival.
2012-12-10|2012-12-16.name: Vol. 16

2012-12-17|2012-12-23.description: Why are Super Dinosaur and Derek Dynamo on the moon? Why not?! There's a dark secret deep below the surface that could spell doom for our heroes... what is 'Inner-Moon?'
Now realizing the shocking truth about her brother, Dana attempts to stop the Joker King while Batman races to the hospital!
2012-12-17|2012-12-23.name: 10,000 Clowns: A Great Gotham Tradition

2012-12-17|2012-12-23.description: The world's heroines are whisked away to the Planet Rann to team up with Hawkgirl and Alana Strange against the mighty and evil Sinestra. Sinestra's focused her attention towards Earth, and these powerful women, armed with a weapon of incalculable power, are the planet's last hope!
2012-12-17|2012-12-23.name: Earth in Crisis, Part 1

2012-12-17|2012-12-23.description:
Cou and Ren have finally made it inside Edel Garden. With the help of former acquaintances, they manage to enter its Central City without encountering any attacks from the Orga Nights. In a secluded area deep inside Edel Garden they find Cia, but their joyful reunion is short lived when Cia reveals her grotesque and mutated figure. Have Cou and Ren walked into a trap? Will they be able to reunite with the Arc Ailes?
